The Rotary Club of Lagos has concluded plans to hold The World Peace and Understanding Day Symposium themed ‘Promoting Peace among Ethnic Nationalities in Nigeria’ on February 23, 2022, at the Nigerian Institute of International Affairs (NIIA) Lagos, from 10:30am. In a release Monday, the club’s President, Babawale Agbeyangi, confirmed that the keynote address would be by Prof. Attahiru Jega, former Chairman, Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). The panellists are Mr Yemi Candide-Johnson (SAN), Rev. Juliet Binitie, Prof. Pat Utomi and Mrs Fayo Williams. The District Governor, Rotary International District 9110, Remi Bello, will also be the special guest. The Chairperson of the World Understanding Day Committee, Gbenga Onabanjo, explained that the event aims to provide a platform for discussions that will help improve understanding and promote peace in Nigeria. He noted that the symposium is in commemoration of the 117th anniversary of the first meeting of Rotary held on February 23, 1905, now designated as the World Understanding and Peace Day. He added that the symposium is also in line with one of the seven focus areas of Rotary, which is peace and conflict prevention/resolution. This focus area is the theme for the month in Rotary worldwide.